Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) have emerged as high temperature fuel cell technology operating at temperatures around 1000 degrees C. Lowering the operating temperature enables the use of cheaper materials while maintaining high power outputs.
Titulo: Effect of B-site doping on electrical conductivity of YAlO3 based electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrolytes with ABO(3)-type perovskite structure are good ionic conductors and are promising materials for SOFCs.
Titulo: Effect of B-site doping on electrical conductivity of YAlO3 based electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In this study, a systematic investigation on the synthesis and characterization of Mg- substituted YAlO3 system has been performed.
Titulo: Effect of B-site doping on electrical conductivity of YAlO3 based electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The samples have been synthesized by wet chemical citrate gel route and the electrical conductivity measurements have been conducted in air between 300 and 800 degrees C. Effect of composition of the phases on total conductivity has been analyzed employing X-ray diffraction.
Titulo: Effect of B-site doping on electrical conductivity of YAlO3 based electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The influence of microstructure on total conductivity has been studied using scanning electron microscopy and orientation imaging microscopy.
Titulo: Effect of B-site doping on electrical conductivity of YAlO3 based electrolytes for solid oxide fuel cells
